    "body": "I would like to express my thoughts of the possible solution. Correct me if i am wrong.\r\nI start HashState from scratch [here](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/blob/master/cmd/integration/main.go#L13). \r\nFirstly, i have to check that i am running \"integration stage_hash_state\" (cause my solution relates to HashStage only)\r\nSecondly, i have to implement the service with inbound channel that is triggered [here](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/blob/c514f9a21463c93fdc5af1e2fb0d260c9cee63d6/cmd/utils/cmd.go#L346). I assume i have to close all resourcers (what exact resourcers?) used in [stageHashState](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/blob/master/cmd/integration/commands/stages.go#L455) if something comes into my inbound channel. In this case i can call some method to release resourcers e.g. ResetHashState ( i am not sure if it's appropriate method for that). Please advice.",
