    "body": "Almost correct. Here is some context: \r\n- integration - is a tool for testing - run each stage individually. Main TurboGeth code starts from https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/blob/master/cmd/tg/main.go\r\n- both TurboGeth and integration tool finally calling https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/blob/master/eth/stagedsync/stage_hashstate.go\r\n- this is where problem exists: we pass “quit” channel there (it notified on ctrl+C), but by some reason this stage doesn’t stop (probably we didn’t use “quit” channel in some long loop). \r\n- About “integration resetHashState” - this command cleaning database tables related to this stage. So, you can use integration (stage_hash_state and reset) for testing. Reset stage and run it from scratch. But target is: to make main TurboGeth process cancelable when it executing this stage. ",
